email_text:
Dear Devanshi, 

I hope you're doing well. 

My name is Tanush Changani, and I am a senior studying computer and data engineering at City University of Hong Kong. I'm inquiring about your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to hear about your experience as a Software Engineer at Google, especially working on GCP Pub/Sub. 

As someone undecided about where to start a career in software engineering, advice from someone with so much experience would be amazing. I'd love to learn from someone who has been working at the intersection of Machine Learning and Software Engineering. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great week! 

Sincerely, 
Tanush Changani

Dear Nihar, 

I hope you're well. 

My name is Tanush Changani, and I am a senior studying computer and data engineering at City University of Hong Kong. I wanted to inquire about your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to hear about your experience at Google and what led you to become a software engineer coming out of Rutgers.

As someone unsure of how to start a career in software engineering, advice from someone like you would be invaluable. I would love to learn more about the work you do at Google, especially the cool software additions on Google Slides and the challenges faced in adding try/catch/finally functionality to the SamboxedJs compiler. 

I've attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week!

Sincerely, 
Tanush Changani

email_text:
Dear Rudransh, 

I hope you are doing well! 

My name is Tanush Changani, and I am a senior studying Computer and Data Engineering at City University of Hong Kong. I am inquiring about your availability for a quick chat in the coming weeks to hear about your experience at Google and why you came to New York from College Station, Texas. 

As someone still figuring out the right way to start a career and overcome the potential challenges, advice on workshops for Open Source Software development would be really amazing. Coming from Hong Kong, I am surrounded by people interested in a similar path but with different perspectives. Thus, understanding the importance of the same opinion would be a great learning for me. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I am looking forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week. 

Best regards, 
Tanush.

email_text:
Dear Sneha, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Tanush Changani, and I am a penultimate year student pursuing a Bachelor's in Computer and Data Engineering at City University of Hong Kong. I am inquiring about your availability for a brief call or coffee in the coming weeks to hear about your experience as a Software Engineer at Sidewalk Labs and Google and learn more about the intersection of technology and sustainability.

As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in software engineering with a focus on sustainability, advice from someone with vast experience would be amazing. Your journey from Pennsylvania to being a part of innovative projects such as Mesa and the live view feature at Google Maps is truly inspiring and I would love to learn from your experience.

I have attached my resume for you to look over. Please let me know if there is a time that works for you, and I would be more than happy to fit into your availability. 

Thank you for considering my request, and I look forward to hearing from you. 

Sincerely, 
Tanush Changani

projects: [{'title': 'Predicting NYC Complaints Using Machine Learning Algorithms', 'date': {'start': {'month': 6, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}, 'end': {'month': 11, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}}, 'description': 'This project seeks to help the Department of Housing Preservation and Development of New York City determine what building and housing complaints to solve using machine learning algorithms and data visualization techniques.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Avi', 'last_name': 'Shah', 'name': None, 'headline': 'SWE @ Google | CS @ GT'}]}, {'title': 'The Effect of Diet on Inflammatory Bowel Disease', 'date': {'start': {'month': 8, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}, 'end': {'month': 6, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}}, 'description': 'In the USA, there are more than 3 million people with Inflammatory Bowel Disease (IBD), and this number is increasing by 0.2 million every year. The purpose of this study was to investigate the association between the intake of certain dietary factors, including specific fruits, vegetables, and sweetened products, and the risk and severity of symptoms of IBD. Data from the National Health and Nutritional Examination Survey (NHANES) was cleaned and analyzed using SAS 9.4. Odds ratio and ordinal logistic regression analyses were performed in order to observe the association between dietary intake and risk of IBD and severity of symptoms in IBD, respectively. Intake of fried potatoes was associated with a decreased risk of IBD (OR 0.71, 95% CI: 0.39, 1.31, p = 0.27). Additionally, intake of vegetables, ice cream, fruit, and non-fried potatoes was associated with an increase in level of severity of symptoms, while intake of chocolate/candy and cookies/cake was associated with a decrease in severity of symptoms. Based on the results, more research must be performed in order to confirm an association between dietary intake and the risk and severity of symptoms of IBD.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Avi', 'last_name': 'Shah', 'name': None, 'headline': 'SWE @ Google | CS @ GT'}]}]

Dear Avi, 

Happy New Year, and I hope you are doing well! 

My name is Tanush Changani, and I am a senior at City University of Hong Kong, majoring in Computer and Data Engineering. I came across your impressive profile and wanted to inquire about your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to hear about your experience at Google and why you chose to pursue a career in Software Engineering.

As someone navigating the complexities of starting a career in tech, advice from someone with so much experience at a company like Google would be invaluable. I am particularly interested in understanding how you find the culture and ethos at Google, including your experience in the software engineering intern role. I'd love to learn more about your experiences between Manulife and Rockset and how you got started on your path at Google.

I have attached my resume for you to look at, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to connecting with you, and once again, Happy New Year!

Sincerely, 
Tanush Changani

email_text:
Dear Samuel, 

I hope you are doing well. 

I am Tanush Changani, a junior studying Computer and Data Engineering at City University of Hong Kong. I am reaching out to inquire about your availability for a quick call in the coming weeks to learn more about your experience at Google and why you decided to pursue a career in software engineering. 

As someone unsure of the next steps in my career, guidance from someone with so much experience would be amazing. I'd love to inquire about your journey at Google, especially having interned there and now working full-time. 

I have attached my resume for you to look at, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. 

Thank you for considering my request, and I look forward to hearing from you soon.

 Sincerely, 

Tanush Changani

My name is Tanush Changani, and I am a penultimate student at City University of Hong Kong, majoring in computer and data engineering. I am writing to inquire about your availability for a quick chat in the coming weeks. 

As someone contemplating a career in software engineering, advice from someone with your experience would be invaluable. I am specifically interested in Google's work on program modularization and expansion of primary status writers. I have attached my resume for your reference, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to the possibility of connecting.

Sincerely, 
Tanush Changani

I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week!

Sincerely, 
Tanush Changani

email_text:
Dear Eumin,

I hope this message finds you well. 

My name is Tanush Changani, and I am a junior at City University of Hong Kong studying Computer and Data Engineering. I am inquiring about your availability for a quick call or a coffee chat in the coming weeks to hear about your experience at Bloomberg and Meta.

As someone still figuring out the right pathway to start a career in software engineering and development, advice from someone with so much experience would be amazing. I would love to learn more about how you transitioned from computer science to industry and Bloomberg's and Meta's Engineering teams.

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I look forward to hearing from you soon. 

Sincerely,
Tanush Changani

email_text:
Dear Christina,

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Tanush Changani, and I am a senior at the City University of Hong Kong, majoring in Computer and Data Engineering. I am writing to inquire about your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to learn more about your experience as a Software Engineer at Meta and why you decided to start a career in New York. 

As someone uncertain about where to begin a career in tech, advice from someone with so much experience would be amazing. I would love to learn from you how working for an SWE role in a vast tech company differs from a startup and the importance of a good product management team. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to the opportunity to speak with you about your journey at Meta and how you came to work there. 

Sincerely, 
Tanush Changani

Tanush Changani

As someone with a deep interest in software development and infrastructure, I am particularly interested in the work you have done in the Facebook Stories Delivery and Ranking Team. Given my passion for backend development, I would love to hear about your experience making Facebook stories more accessible for billions of users.

I look forward to the possibility of speaking with you and hope you have a great rest of your week!

Tanush Changani

Dear Matthew, 

I hope you are doing well.

My name is Tanush, and I am a senior studying computer and data engineering at CityU in Hong Kong. I am inquiring about your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to hear about your experience at Meta and why you came to software engineering from finance? 

As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in software engineering, advice from someone with so much experience would be amazing! I would love to learn more about how you chose engineering from the finance background, and why you decided to start your career in software engineering at a company like Meta. 

I am attaching my resume for your reference, and I am happy to work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to hearing from you!

Sincerely,
Tanush Changani

summary:
I am currently pursuing my Master of Science in Computer Science degree at Northwestern University. Over the course of my professional journey, I have gained experience in both product management and software development. As a Product Manager, I have had the opportunity to develop a diverse skill set, including experience in K-12 AI education at TAL and working at LinkedIn, where I led the launch of two MVPs for young professionals. At TAL, I gathered customer requirements and worked collaboratively with teams to implement effective solutions. At LinkedIn, I honed my skills in data-driven decision-making and team management. My journey continued at Credit Suisse, where I took on a variety of roles in UI/UX design, programming, project management, and product management. During my time there, I optimized a global job rotation platform and contributed to data engineering, which further enhanced my skills and versatility. My most recent role was as a Software Developer at Amazon, where I worked on building a tool for monitoring machine learning models for Alexa and gained valuable insights into software development. 

My primary areas of interest within the industry include electronic consumer products, IoT, AI, VR/AR, big data, and education.

email_text:
Dear Iris,

I hope you are doing well.

My name is Tanush Changani, and I am a final-year Computer and Data Engineering student at the City University of Hong Kong. I wanted to express my interest in contacting you for a quick chat or an email exchange to learn more about your experience transitioning from product management to a full-time position at PAX Technology.

As someone with a keen interest in the intersection of software development and financial technology, I have been considering a similar career path. I'd love to get your insight on CX designs and how you have adapted to the fast-paced nature of the financial technology industry. Could you please let me know a time that works for you in the coming weeks?

I've attached my resume for your reference, and I look forward to the possibility of picking your brain in the near future.

Sincerely, 
Tanush Changani

summary:
Hi! 
Iâ€™m Aliris, a 4th year M&T student getting my Bachelor degrees in CS and Management and my Masters in Data Science.  
Energy transition and electrification is where I want to be.... Currently fascinated by energy storage/batteries, EVs, and China. Looking for opportunities that connect and continue my interests post-grad!

---

I took a gap year after my freshman year when COVID hit and allowed myself to explore, trying software engineering and product roles at startups like The Boring Company, Elio, and big companies like LinkedIn. 

I discovered and fell in love with startups and climate tech then, and have made working on climate my priority ever since.
I started, grew, and transitioned Pennâ€™s first climate tech hub with Andrew Yu and Mark Wasuwanich (+ many others)! On top of creating a community for students interested in climate tech, we organized educational and professional events, semester-long climate consulting projects, and an annual pitch competition.    
While TPMing on Metaâ€™s Storage team, I got involved with their sustainability org, learning about their carbon offset purchase process and carbon accounting practices.
Wanting to see the â€œother sideâ€ of startups and to understand a different market, I found myself investing in semiconductor/semi-adjacent industries in China last summer, including many parts of the EV supply chain.

email_text:
Dear Aliris,

I hope you're doing well. 

My name is Tanush Changani, and I'm a junior studying computer engineering at City University of Hong Kong. I am majoring in Data Engineering, and I want to inquire about your availability for a quick call in the coming weeks to hear about your experience at Crusoe and why you decided to pursue a career in Product Management.

As someone interested in both Software Development and Product Management, I would appreciate the opportunity to learn from your experiences. Specifically, I would like to get advice on how to combine these two fields effectively. 

I have attached my resume for your reference, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits for you. I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week.

Sincerely, 
Tanush Changani

summary:
Shyvee is a product management and corporate innovation expert, currently serves as a Product Lead at LinkedIn and an instructor on LinkedIn Learning. She has impacted over 100K followers and her content has reached 40M views. Her PM Learning Series has featured esteemed guests including the cofounders and Chief Product Officers at top Silicon Valley startups. As President of the Kellogg Alumni Club in San Francisco, Shyvee is a popular speaker and has influenced digital strategies at VMware, Disney, Cisco, YMCA, Toyota, HSBC, Telstra and many Fortune 1000 companies.

Shyvee is the coauthor of Amazon bestseller â€œReimagined: Building Products with Generative AIâ€, an extensive guide for integrating generative AI into product strategy and careers featuring over 150 real-world examples, 30 case studies, and 20+ frameworks, and endorsed by leading AI and product executives, inventors, entrepreneurs, and researchers. Learn more: https://a.co/d/btmnJfu

email_text:
Dear Shyvee, 

I hope that you are well. 

My name is Tanush Changani, and I am a senior studying Computer and Data Engineering at City University of Hong Kong. I am inquiring about your availability for a brief call or coffee in the coming weeks to hear about your experience as a product lead at Microsoft and why you came to tech from consulting. As someone unsure of the best way to start a career in PM, advice from someone with so much experience would be amazing! 

I have attached my resume for your reference, and I would gladly work with your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to hearing from you and hope you have a great rest of your week! 

Best regards, 
Tanush Changani

email_text:
Dear Alice, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Tanush Changani, and I am a junior studying computer and data engineering at City University of Hong Kong. I am vigorously in pursuit of a career in quantitative development and would like to learn more about your experience at Citadel.

In particular, I am interested in understanding how you've adjusted the complex credit market at Citadel using quantitative methods and the challenges you have faced as a full-time Quantitative Developer. As someone exploring different ways to develop a career in this space, I am curious to know how your experience at Sciences Po helped shape your understanding of the intersection between politics and finance. 

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly accommodate your schedule for a call at your convenience. I look forward to your favorable response so that we can connect and learn more about the quantitative development field from someone as experienced as you.

Sincerely, 
Tanush Changani

email_text:
Dear Hojeannie,

I hope you are doing well.

My name is Tanush Changani, a penultimate year Computer and Data Engineering student at City University of Hong Kong. I aspire to combine my technical skills with my passion for solving real-world problems through technology, especially in the areas of AI and machine learning.

I am impressed by your extensive experience at Netflix, especially your work in using AI to enhance user experiences. I am particularly interested in your experience at Amazon and Microsoft and the transition from technical to management roles at Amazon. As someone unsure about the best way to start a tech career, I'd love to hear about your experience and how it has shaped roles like mine.

Would you be available for a quick call in the coming weeks for me to learn from your experience and advice on breaking into the tech industry? I would be more than happy to work around your schedule for a time that suits you best.

I have attached my resume for your reference, and I look forward to hearing from you soon.

Sincerely,
Tanush Changani

sub_title: Product @ Roblox - Former Google, Apple, Nest, Netflix
summary:
With over 10 years of experience in building products, I am passionate about creating innovative and engaging products that connect and empower people across the world. As the Principal Product Manager at Roblox, I lead the Communication Expression team, which aims to enable 1B+ users to communicate and express themselves freely and naturally in the digital realm, while staying safe and civil.

Our team works on user-facing UI for all voice, text and camera tracking to animate avatars on Roblox, from user discovery/ onboarding to safety platform and tooling, with a focus on spatial voice moderation, and audio ML innovation to detect and prevent abuse and automate moderation in real-time. 

In recent years, I have successfully leveraged my skills and expertise in UI design, computer vision, natural language processing, and machine learning to deliver features and solutions that enhance the user experience and satisfaction.

email_text:
Dear Effie, 

I hope your week is going well. 

My name is Tanush Changani, a senior student at City University of Hong Kong studying Computer and Data Engineering. I am writing to inquire about your availability for a short call or coffee in the coming weeks to discuss your journey and perspectives.

I would love to learn more about how you made the shift from perception and computer vision solutions to leading cross PA efforts for shipping new products/features at Google. Coming from a more technical background, advice around transitioning into Product Management would be invaluable. 

I have attached my resume for your convenience, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. 

Thank you for considering my request, and I look forward to hearing from you. 

Sincerely, 

Tanush Changani

sub_title: Netflix AI Product Manager (Creative Algorithms and GenAI) | Fm. Twitter (Group PM - Deep Learning) | ML Research/Eng leader | 8 years applied research in Generative AI
summary:
Pioneer in Generative AI, focused on applied research and product development to augment human creativity and empower artists. ML/AI product leader with extensive experience formulating deep learning models for practical applications. Partnering with Academy Award and Emmy-winning film directors and technologists. Currently implementing generative algorithms and other forms of creative ML to meet the needs of filmmakers and game developers. 

--

My personal mission is to honor and elevate human creativity and art direction, through a combination of artist-centric design and AI. At Netflix, I lead the development of deep learning, graphics/simulation, and imaging products to advance studio production, visual effects/Post, and imaging technology. I have the privilege to work with filmmakers and artists as we unlock new modes of creative expression with AI, together. 

Before Netflix, I led Twitter's computer vision products and product strategy, including direct partnership with the CTO. There, I led media understanding to promote the public conversation. Part of this role was recommending content that sparks engagement, inspiration and curiosity. To do that, we used multi-modal AI to understand images, video, audio, and language holistically - closer to the way humans do. I also led R&D on generative AI for content creation.

Prior to Twitter, I spent time as an engineering manager and in executive leadership. On the eng side, I worked hands-on with SWEs and researchers (eg, implementing and productizing one of the earliest interactive GANs). I also spent time partnering directly with Fortune 100 C-suites to guide their most critical tech investments. 

Outside the day job, I've been a technical advisor to AI startups in pioneering domains, like spatiotemporal deep learning for brain-computer interfaces, and presented at ML conferences (e.g., on deep reinforcement learning). 

Selected past work:
--Partnering with artists to formulate creative workflows - maximizing the expressiveness of generative AI to augment human creativity
--Interactive generative adversarial networks (GAN) for AI-augmented creative design
--Multi-modal embeddings for recommending, ranking, and search algorithms (computer vision, NLP, and graph embeddings, factorization machines, learning-to-rank)
--Human pose estimation, action recognition, and emotion detection from live video
--Spatiotemporal deep learning for signal processing, video classification, and brain-computer interfaces
--State-of-the-art speech and natural language processing for virtual agents

Dear James, 

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Tanush Changani, and I am a senior at City University of Hong Kong, majoring in Computer and Data Engineering. I am interested in AI and ML, especially in their applications for creative media, and was impressed by your extensive work experience at Netflix and Twitter. 

As someone still charting his course in the field, I'd greatly appreciate your insights on how AI-driven decisions are made in the media industry, and how businesses quantify the impact of these decisions. Besides, I am curious about the innovative work Netflix is doing to enhance the creative process for filmmakers and artists. 

I have attached my resume for your reference, and I would be thrilled to work around your schedule for a call or a coffee chat in the coming weeks to hear about your journey and experiences. 

I look forward to connecting and hope you have a great week ahead. 

Sincerely, 
Tanush Changani

email_text:
Dear Mr Ghalib,

I hope you are doing well. 

My name is Tanush Changani, and I am a final year Computer and Data Engineering student at the City University of Hong Kong. I am writing to inquire about your availability for a quick call or coffee in the coming weeks to hear about your experience at Netflix and Google, and why you decided to move from Project Management at Google to Business Development at Netflix.

As someone who is unsure about the best way to start a career in tech business relations, advice from someone with so much experience would be amazing. Over the past year, I have developed a keen interest in the business side of tech, and the information on your LinkedIn about your new role makes me even more curious.

I have attached my resume for you to look over, and I would gladly work around your schedule to find a time that fits. I look forward to your positive response and hope you have a great week.

Sincerely,
Tanush Changani
